The paper proposes a deep learning-based motion planning model for autonomous vehicles using spatiotemporal LSTM network. The model extracts spatiotemporal information from sequential image data using Conv-LSTM and 3D-CNN and constructs a control model for autonomous vehicle steering angle using fully connected neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with autonomous vehicle navigation, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning techniques for motion planning also suggests that the paper could be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with real-life traffic situations and uncertainty, which suggests that it could also be categorized under Systems and Control (cs.SY).
